1
00:00:14,480 --> 00:00:17,440
♪In the airport lounge
at the break of day♪

2
00:00:18,040 --> 00:00:22,200
♪A page of dust beneath my fingers♪

3
00:00:22,560 --> 00:00:25,160
♪Filled with stories♪

4
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:28,280
♪That others never got to tell♪

5
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,960
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

6
00:00:33,040 --> 00:00:35,600
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

7
00:00:35,680 --> 00:00:37,160
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

8
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:40,040
♪The world is split an inch wider♪

9
00:00:40,080 --> 00:00:42,600
♪Raise your eyes, face the light♪

10
00:00:42,760 --> 00:00:45,080
♪See the truth, and see the fright♪

11
00:00:45,280 --> 00:00:46,800
♪Guard the crack within this door♪

12
00:00:46,840 --> 00:00:52,600
♪Keep the way back home
always burning bright♪

13
00:00:54,520 --> 00:00:57,040
♪The camera pans
across the boarding crowd♪

14
00:00:57,080 --> 00:00:59,200
♪Some wear a smile,
some have their eyes adrift♪

15
00:00:59,280 --> 00:01:01,360
♪A red suitcase♪

16
00:01:01,440 --> 00:01:05,360
♪Tied with faded pasts
and broken prayers♪

17
00:01:06,720 --> 00:01:09,360
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

18
00:01:09,480 --> 00:01:12,080
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

19
00:01:12,160 --> 00:01:13,960
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

20
00:01:14,040 --> 00:01:17,400
♪It's the heartbeat
echoing the call of law♪

21
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:30,000
[Gimlet Eyes]

22
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:33,000
[Episode 7]

23
00:01:35,070 --> 00:01:35,930
Mr. Huang,

24
00:01:36,430 --> 00:01:37,540
we're not here

25
00:01:37,560 --> 00:01:38,900
to play heroes.

26
00:01:39,560 --> 00:01:41,020
We're here to stop criminals

27
00:01:41,040 --> 00:01:42,210
before things get out of control.

28
00:01:42,480 --> 00:01:43,660
If we

29
00:01:43,680 --> 00:01:45,130
let them go unchecked,

30
00:01:45,480 --> 00:01:46,290
it'll set off

31
00:01:46,510 --> 00:01:47,850
a ripple effect

32
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:49,180
across society

33
00:01:49,200 --> 00:01:50,620
and trigger a chain reaction

34
00:01:51,280 --> 00:01:52,850
that drags lots of innocent people

35
00:01:52,870 --> 00:01:53,980
down with it.

36
00:01:54,950 --> 00:01:56,050
You're a father.

37
00:01:56,870 --> 00:01:58,820
I'm sure you want your kid to grow up

38
00:01:58,870 --> 00:01:59,930
in a world

39
00:01:59,950 --> 00:02:01,980
that's safer and brighter.

40
00:02:02,430 --> 00:02:03,770
She deserves to grow up carefree

41
00:02:03,790 --> 00:02:04,850
in the sunlight,

42
00:02:05,150 --> 00:02:06,210
not on edge every second

43
00:02:06,760 --> 00:02:08,010
like you are.

44
00:02:08,030 --> 00:02:08,540
Don't you think?

45
00:02:15,520 --> 00:02:16,260
Fine.

46
00:02:17,560 --> 00:02:19,540
I'll talk, okay?

47
00:02:22,910 --> 00:02:24,170
The guy who placed the order

48
00:02:24,430 --> 00:02:25,500
was about my height

49
00:02:25,560 --> 00:02:26,730
and around my age.

50
00:02:27,120 --> 00:02:28,340
He went by

51
00:02:29,280 --> 00:02:29,850
Hong Fei.

52
00:02:30,960 --> 00:02:32,100
Probably a fake name.

53
00:02:32,240 --> 00:02:33,570
He looked pretty decent,

54
00:02:33,800 --> 00:02:35,820
wearing rimless glasses

55
00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:38,570
and a three-piece suit.

56
00:02:38,800 --> 00:02:40,690
Didn't look like a smuggler at all.

57
00:02:41,870 --> 00:02:42,410
Oh,

58
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:44,010
he had a long scar

59
00:02:44,560 --> 00:02:45,890
on his left wrist.

60
00:02:46,190 --> 00:02:47,730
I saw it when he handed me the cash.

61
00:02:47,870 --> 00:02:49,130
If you saw him again,

62
00:02:49,190 --> 00:02:50,130
would you recognize him?

63
00:02:50,150 --> 00:02:50,890
Of course.

64
00:02:50,910 --> 00:02:52,260
Did he mention anything else

65
00:02:52,280 --> 00:02:54,130
besides the cup

66
00:02:54,150 --> 00:02:55,820
while you were talking?

67
00:02:55,910 --> 00:02:57,450
No, just the cup.

68
00:02:57,470 --> 00:02:58,570
Nothing else.

69
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:00,170
But

70
00:03:00,590 --> 00:03:02,060
the way he spoke…

71
00:03:02,590 --> 00:03:03,820
His choice of words

72
00:03:05,470 --> 00:03:06,260
was precise.

73
00:03:07,080 --> 00:03:07,980
Very precise.

74
00:03:09,310 --> 00:03:09,890
Mr. Huang,

75
00:03:10,520 --> 00:03:11,570
I need to ask you a favor.

76
00:03:11,590 --> 00:03:13,060
Please go to Customs ASAP.

77
00:03:13,190 --> 00:03:14,340
Report everything you know

78
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:16,220
to the anti-smuggling officer

79
00:03:16,470 --> 00:03:17,380
who contacted you last time.

80
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:18,100
No problem.

81
00:03:18,310 --> 00:03:18,980
I'll go tomorrow,

82
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:20,100
right after I drop my kid off.

83
00:03:20,120 --> 00:03:20,450
That work?

84
00:03:20,470 --> 00:03:20,820
That works.

85
00:03:21,280 --> 00:03:21,980
Are we done?

86
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:22,410
Yes.

87
00:03:22,560 --> 00:03:23,170
Can I go now?

88
00:03:23,190 --> 00:03:23,570
Yes.

89
00:03:25,840 --> 00:03:26,610
Mr. Huang.

90
00:03:30,120 --> 00:03:31,570
You've done us a big favor.

91
00:03:31,590 --> 00:03:33,130
Let me do you a small favor.

92
00:03:33,430 --> 00:03:33,940
You? Help me?

93
00:03:33,960 --> 00:03:35,100
Just don't make things harder for me.

94
00:03:35,150 --> 00:03:35,660
Here.

95
00:03:36,150 --> 00:03:36,940
Take this.

96
00:03:38,030 --> 00:03:39,060
I've already made a call.

97
00:03:39,400 --> 00:03:40,220
He should have

98
00:03:40,400 --> 00:03:41,010
some orders

99
00:03:41,030 --> 00:03:42,730
that fit your factory.

100
00:03:43,240 --> 00:03:43,980
Xiang Xiuyuan?

101
00:03:44,400 --> 00:03:45,690
Xiangliang Trading Company.

102
00:03:48,590 --> 00:03:50,290
This isn't something small.

103
00:03:50,430 --> 00:03:51,850
This is a huge favor!

104
00:03:52,590 --> 00:03:53,130
Thank you.

105
00:03:53,870 --> 00:03:54,570
Thank you!

106
00:03:57,000 --> 00:03:58,060
Can I go now?

107
00:03:58,080 --> 00:03:59,060
Go ahead.

108
00:03:59,750 --> 00:04:00,540
Thank you.

109
00:04:02,430 --> 00:04:04,100
Don't forget to go to Customs tomorrow.

110
00:04:04,360 --> 00:04:05,010
Don't worry.

111
00:04:05,030 --> 00:04:05,730
I'll be there.

112
00:04:05,750 --> 00:04:06,540
Thanks!

113
00:04:14,030 --> 00:04:14,820
What's wrong?

114
00:04:15,590 --> 00:04:17,170
We just got a solid lead.

115
00:04:17,560 --> 00:04:18,370
Aren't you happy about it?

116
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:34,580
I'm just pissed.

117
00:04:35,070 --> 00:04:36,610
People like Huang Qiang

118
00:04:37,040 --> 00:04:38,250
help smugglers

119
00:04:38,310 --> 00:04:40,410
for a little personal gain.

120
00:04:41,750 --> 00:04:42,930
Truth is, everyone

121
00:04:43,830 --> 00:04:44,900
has desires.

122
00:04:45,190 --> 00:04:46,250
But not everyone

123
00:04:46,270 --> 00:04:47,700
can keep them under control.

124
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:50,170
Smugglers

125
00:04:50,390 --> 00:04:51,930
exploit that weakness,

126
00:04:52,750 --> 00:04:53,540
dangle a little money,

127
00:04:54,190 --> 00:04:56,140
and turn them into pawns.

128
00:04:56,600 --> 00:04:58,020
If I'm guessing right,

129
00:04:58,080 --> 00:04:59,020
I'd say

130
00:04:59,870 --> 00:05:01,900
the guy who placed that order
is no different.

131
00:05:01,960 --> 00:05:03,580
You think he's a pawn, too?

132
00:05:03,950 --> 00:05:04,540
Think about it.

133
00:05:05,270 --> 00:05:06,340
Huang Qiang said

134
00:05:06,640 --> 00:05:08,930
there's a scar on his left wrist.

135
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:11,220
Could be self-inflicted.

136
00:05:11,280 --> 00:05:12,290
That means he's

137
00:05:12,520 --> 00:05:13,490
hit rock bottom before.

138
00:05:14,390 --> 00:05:16,250
If smugglers caught him at that point

139
00:05:16,270 --> 00:05:17,250
and dangled the right bait,

140
00:05:17,640 --> 00:05:18,730
he'd fall for it

141
00:05:19,040 --> 00:05:20,140
if he couldn't resist.

142
00:05:20,200 --> 00:05:20,930
Don't you think?

143
00:05:20,950 --> 00:05:23,340
Then the ones setting the bait
are even worse!

144
00:05:25,280 --> 00:05:26,610
We size people up every day

145
00:05:26,630 --> 00:05:28,170
in Customs.

146
00:05:28,430 --> 00:05:29,780
But smugglers

147
00:05:30,190 --> 00:05:31,490
do the same.

148
00:05:32,040 --> 00:05:33,580
They're scanning crowds

149
00:05:33,640 --> 00:05:35,290
for vulnerable people
they can use as pawns.

150
00:05:35,630 --> 00:05:36,410
Think about it.

151
00:05:36,960 --> 00:05:38,020
Every year,

152
00:05:38,070 --> 00:05:39,980
we catch a lot of smugglers at Customs.

153
00:05:40,400 --> 00:05:42,050
Most are just mules.

154
00:05:42,960 --> 00:05:44,780
From a smuggler's perspective,

155
00:05:45,040 --> 00:05:45,780
mules are cheap

156
00:05:46,040 --> 00:05:47,250
and disposable.

157
00:05:47,720 --> 00:05:48,700
What a mule gets paid

158
00:05:48,760 --> 00:05:50,540
is nothing compared to

159
00:05:50,840 --> 00:05:52,170
what the ring makes.

160
00:05:52,750 --> 00:05:54,370
People like Huang Qiang
may be despicable,

161
00:05:54,510 --> 00:05:55,140
but

162
00:05:55,840 --> 00:05:56,850
the ones behind him,

163
00:05:57,040 --> 00:05:58,140
preying on human weakness,

164
00:05:58,510 --> 00:05:59,900
are the worst of them all.

165
00:06:03,270 --> 00:06:04,540
You mean

166
00:06:05,480 --> 00:06:06,660
the handlers?

167
00:06:09,430 --> 00:06:10,290
Remember this.

168
00:06:11,040 --> 00:06:12,100
No one's perfect.

169
00:06:12,720 --> 00:06:13,610
Everyone

170
00:06:13,630 --> 00:06:14,660
has cracks.

171
00:06:15,040 --> 00:06:17,460
And what gets into those cracks
isn't always light.

172
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:21,220
A handler is someone
who stuffs darkness into them.

173
00:06:24,230 --> 00:06:26,820
So helping Huang Qiang find a job

174
00:06:28,040 --> 00:06:29,970
was your way of letting the light in?

175
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:35,660
I just happened to be able to help.

176
00:06:35,950 --> 00:06:38,540
To patch that crack, at least for now.

177
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:42,930
That still counts as light.

178
00:06:55,160 --> 00:06:56,730
Each bag stays on the belt

179
00:06:56,750 --> 00:06:57,700
for just three to five seconds.

180
00:06:57,720 --> 00:06:59,370
You only get one shot. Don't miss it.

181
00:06:59,750 --> 00:07:01,290
It has to be airtight.

182
00:07:01,830 --> 00:07:03,050
One slip,
and the whole thing falls apart.

183
00:07:04,560 --> 00:07:05,540
This one's off.

184
00:07:06,070 --> 00:07:07,020
Could be a specimen.

185
00:07:07,870 --> 00:07:08,660
Sir.

186
00:07:08,870 --> 00:07:09,610
China Customs.

187
00:07:10,270 --> 00:07:11,250
Please open the case.

188
00:07:11,270 --> 00:07:12,290
We need to take a closer look.

189
00:07:15,720 --> 00:07:17,810
Per regulations,
insect specimens are prohibited

190
00:07:17,830 --> 00:07:19,140
without prior approval
from the relevant authorities.

191
00:07:20,630 --> 00:07:21,410
Insect specimen.

192
00:07:23,120 --> 00:07:24,140
And look,

193
00:07:24,630 --> 00:07:25,780
this is fruit.

194
00:07:28,390 --> 00:07:29,660
There's fruit in your luggage.

195
00:07:29,680 --> 00:07:30,730
That's prohibited

196
00:07:30,870 --> 00:07:32,290
under the relevant regulations.

197
00:07:39,830 --> 00:07:40,580
That one's off too.

198
00:07:40,720 --> 00:07:41,460
Could be ivory

199
00:07:41,480 --> 00:07:43,370
or some kind of wood product.

200
00:07:44,070 --> 00:07:44,980
Come with me, this way.

201
00:07:52,120 --> 00:07:54,290
Ivory products are not permitted entry.

202
00:07:56,480 --> 00:07:57,460
Prohibited.

203
00:08:00,680 --> 00:08:01,410
Khat.

204
00:08:03,920 --> 00:08:04,780
Dayu,

205
00:08:05,040 --> 00:08:08,140
your scan reads are unreal.

206
00:08:09,070 --> 00:08:10,580
Don't hype me up.

207
00:08:10,750 --> 00:08:12,170
This is basic stuff.

208
00:08:12,600 --> 00:08:13,490
Your mentor's always

209
00:08:13,510 --> 00:08:15,170
talking about sizing people up
at a glance,

210
00:08:15,310 --> 00:08:16,730
but when it comes to scanning images,

211
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:18,610
I'd be his mentor.

212
00:08:19,560 --> 00:08:20,540
What about Shihuo?

213
00:08:21,270 --> 00:08:22,980
Hard to say.

214
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:24,050
We're about even.

215
00:08:25,160 --> 00:08:26,900
Let's just say I'm the up-and-comer,

216
00:08:26,920 --> 00:08:28,900
and I outshine him every now and then.

217
00:08:30,560 --> 00:08:31,220
However,

218
00:08:31,600 --> 00:08:33,770
what I respect most
is that mouth of yours.

219
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:38,010
Not too late to switch
to the right mentor.

220
00:08:41,150 --> 00:08:41,610
Let's go.

221
00:08:43,960 --> 00:08:44,850
How's it looking?

222
00:08:45,910 --> 00:08:46,850
All clear.

223
00:09:22,360 --> 00:09:23,460
Excuse me, China Customs.

224
00:09:23,480 --> 00:09:24,340
Inspection, please.

225
00:09:24,360 --> 00:09:25,940
What's this about?

226
00:09:25,960 --> 00:09:27,890
Excuse me, customs inspection.

227
00:09:28,750 --> 00:09:29,770
Why are you stopping me?

228
00:09:29,790 --> 00:09:31,460
Sorry, sir, you have to go there.

229
00:09:31,600 --> 00:09:32,460
That's the rule.

230
00:09:34,790 --> 00:09:38,220
I don't understand you. What's going on?

231
00:09:38,240 --> 00:09:38,940
Please open it.

232
00:09:39,270 --> 00:09:39,890
By yourself.

233
00:09:45,510 --> 00:09:48,180
I've never been stopped before.

234
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:50,770
It's just a carpet I bought.

235
00:09:50,790 --> 00:09:53,490
What gives you the right to stop me?

236
00:09:53,840 --> 00:09:57,580
I'll file a complaint.

237
00:09:57,640 --> 00:10:00,100
I have never once been stopped.

238
00:10:00,160 --> 00:10:03,650
Do you realize the consequences?

239
00:10:03,670 --> 00:10:05,420
Dear passenger, please come with me.

240
00:10:06,630 --> 00:10:07,940
And who are you?

241
00:10:08,240 --> 00:10:09,770
I've said it multiple times.

242
00:10:09,790 --> 00:10:10,420
Sorry, sir.

243
00:10:10,480 --> 00:10:11,610
Can you speak English?

244
00:10:12,160 --> 00:10:13,700
I've said it over and over.

245
00:10:13,880 --> 00:10:15,890
I can't understand you.

246
00:10:15,910 --> 00:10:18,580
I've got something urgent to deal with.
I need to go now.

247
00:10:18,640 --> 00:10:19,420
Look at you,

248
00:10:19,480 --> 00:10:21,580
all that language training,

249
00:10:21,640 --> 00:10:22,700
and you can't crack this one.

250
00:10:23,510 --> 00:10:24,300
Get an interpreter. Now.

251
00:10:25,120 --> 00:10:25,820
Mr. Guo,

252
00:10:26,280 --> 00:10:28,100
he doesn't look suspicious.

253
00:10:28,910 --> 00:10:31,060
Getting a rare-language interpreter
takes time.

254
00:10:31,120 --> 00:10:32,940
We shouldn't hold him up
too long, right?

255
00:10:34,510 --> 00:10:35,490
Fair point.

256
00:10:35,630 --> 00:10:36,730
Maybe we should

257
00:10:37,120 --> 00:10:37,940
let him go?

258
00:10:40,160 --> 00:10:40,850
Thank you.

259
00:10:41,030 --> 00:10:42,580
So you do understand Chinese.

260
00:10:43,440 --> 00:10:45,220
Sir, China Customs.

261
00:10:45,280 --> 00:10:46,610
This way, please.

262
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:55,060
Get Zhou Bing.
Bring in the drug sniffer dog.

263
00:11:00,760 --> 00:11:01,490
Excuse me.

264
00:11:09,550 --> 00:11:10,060
Turn right.

265
00:11:13,910 --> 00:11:14,420
Keep up.

266
00:11:17,750 --> 00:11:18,730
Don't touch it.

267
00:11:19,280 --> 00:11:21,220
Why are you detaining my luggage?

268
00:11:21,280 --> 00:11:22,890
This carpet is just a gift.

269
00:11:23,480 --> 00:11:24,940
Now you can speak English?

270
00:11:28,150 --> 00:11:29,100
According to

271
00:11:29,630 --> 00:11:30,770
the X-ray,

272
00:11:31,280 --> 00:11:32,340
this carpet contains

273
00:11:32,630 --> 00:11:33,730
an unknown

274
00:11:33,870 --> 00:11:34,820
white powder.

275
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:35,940
We have reason to believe

276
00:11:36,270 --> 00:11:38,420
this is more than just a gift.

277
00:11:38,870 --> 00:11:39,940
Through the X-ray,

278
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:40,580
we found that

279
00:11:40,640 --> 00:11:43,890
there are a large number of
unknown items hidden in your carpet.

280
00:11:44,280 --> 00:11:45,250
We have reason to believe

281
00:11:45,270 --> 00:11:46,610
this is not a 'gift'.

282
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:48,820
This is just bamboo fiber.

283
00:11:49,120 --> 00:11:51,220
You're wronging a good person.

284
00:11:53,040 --> 00:11:54,100
Mr. Guo, we're here.

285
00:11:55,280 --> 00:11:55,890
Thanks for coming.

286
00:11:56,160 --> 00:11:57,530
Hu, sniff.

287
00:11:57,790 --> 00:11:58,370
Sniff.

288
00:12:11,120 --> 00:12:11,700
I just said

289
00:12:11,760 --> 00:12:12,610
there's nothing.

290
00:12:21,150 --> 00:12:24,100
This carpet is quite expensive stuff,
you know?

291
00:12:24,160 --> 00:12:27,580
What are you… This cost 200,000 euros.

292
00:12:27,670 --> 00:12:31,300
If you destroy it,
you'll pay twice as much as it cost.

293
00:12:31,320 --> 00:12:33,650
We know, sir.
Please sit down. Calm down.

294
00:12:35,390 --> 00:12:37,010
As a Customs officer,

295
00:12:37,030 --> 00:12:37,940
I'll answer your question directly.

296
00:12:38,750 --> 00:12:41,340
I need to cut open your carpet
for inspection.

297
00:12:41,550 --> 00:12:43,980
I will assume full legal responsibility.

298
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:56,420
Are you crazy?
You're violating my rights!

299
00:12:56,440 --> 00:12:58,580
I'll let you lose your job!

300
00:12:58,600 --> 00:13:00,060
Sir, sit down!

301
00:13:36,600 --> 00:13:38,060
We now have evidence

302
00:13:38,480 --> 00:13:39,730
that the carpet you're carrying

303
00:13:40,150 --> 00:13:42,060
contains substances
prohibited from entering China.

304
00:13:42,550 --> 00:13:44,060
Please cooperate with the Chinese police

305
00:13:44,080 --> 00:13:45,850
and the Customs anti-smuggling unit.

306
00:13:47,320 --> 00:13:49,460
China Customs has evidence to prove

307
00:13:49,480 --> 00:13:51,650
that your carpet has prohibited item

308
00:13:51,670 --> 00:13:53,890
that is not allowed
to enter our country.

309
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:55,730
Please cooperate with our

310
00:13:55,960 --> 00:13:57,610
anti-smuggling unit.

311
00:14:05,960 --> 00:14:06,770
That woman

312
00:14:07,480 --> 00:14:08,940
is Zhang Dayu's wife, Zhou Bing.

313
00:14:09,440 --> 00:14:11,130
Nothing like Dayu's big mouth.

314
00:14:11,150 --> 00:14:12,700
Bing is seriously cool.

315
00:14:13,440 --> 00:14:15,850
Mentor, I was a nervous wreck just now.

316
00:14:16,270 --> 00:14:17,580
A 200,000-euro carpet,

317
00:14:17,600 --> 00:14:18,890
and you cut it open without hesitation.

318
00:14:19,320 --> 00:14:20,940
What if there was nothing inside?

319
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:22,180
No 'what ifs'.

320
00:14:22,200 --> 00:14:23,980
The X-ray flagged an anomaly.

321
00:14:24,080 --> 00:14:25,250
We needed to check further.

322
00:14:25,550 --> 00:14:27,100
Can you walk me through your reasoning?

323
00:14:28,030 --> 00:14:30,130
His baggage barcode showed

324
00:14:30,360 --> 00:14:31,940
he came through Amsterdam.

325
00:14:32,200 --> 00:14:34,100
That's a major
international drug transit hub.

326
00:14:34,600 --> 00:14:36,460
And I handled the carpet myself.

327
00:14:36,510 --> 00:14:37,580
It's nowhere near 200,000 euros.

328
00:14:37,910 --> 00:14:39,650
But he kept insisting it was.

329
00:14:39,750 --> 00:14:41,610
That's a bluff.

330
00:14:41,720 --> 00:14:42,700
He was trying to
scare us off opening it.

331
00:14:43,270 --> 00:14:44,250
And the clincher is,

332
00:14:44,270 --> 00:14:45,530
last month in Toronto, Canada,

333
00:14:45,840 --> 00:14:46,820
there was a bust

334
00:14:46,910 --> 00:14:48,530
involving drugs hidden
inside a carpet shipped by mail.

335
00:14:50,150 --> 00:14:51,180
Bold and sharp.

336
00:14:51,200 --> 00:14:52,100
Solid logic.

337
00:14:52,390 --> 00:14:52,940
Respect.

338
00:14:54,200 --> 00:14:54,850
Mentor,

339
00:14:55,480 --> 00:14:57,220
how did you know about

340
00:14:57,240 --> 00:14:58,130
that Toronto carpet case?

341
00:14:58,200 --> 00:15:00,060
Your English is better than mine,
and you're younger.

342
00:15:00,150 --> 00:15:01,580
You should've known about it
before I did.

343
00:15:04,480 --> 00:15:05,890
My wife told me

344
00:15:06,390 --> 00:15:08,610
Hu was completely thrown off.

345
00:15:09,720 --> 00:15:10,460
You know?

346
00:15:10,750 --> 00:15:12,730
He went in for a sniff and got nothing.

347
00:15:13,390 --> 00:15:15,890
For a top-notch drug sniffer dog,

348
00:15:15,910 --> 00:15:17,220
that's a real hit to his confidence.

349
00:15:17,240 --> 00:15:18,460
That's gotta hurt.

350
00:15:18,480 --> 00:15:19,490
- Yeah. - Of course.

351
00:15:19,510 --> 00:15:20,340
Give me a hand here.

352
00:15:20,550 --> 00:15:22,130
Look at you. Now you're an expert.

353
00:15:22,240 --> 00:15:24,060
You can even read a dog's mind now.

354
00:15:25,360 --> 00:15:26,220
Of course.

355
00:15:26,630 --> 00:15:27,460
Think about it.

356
00:15:27,630 --> 00:15:29,300
Dogs can actually sense

357
00:15:29,320 --> 00:15:30,220
their handler's emotions.

358
00:15:30,790 --> 00:15:31,850
I know my wife better than anyone.

359
00:15:31,960 --> 00:15:33,300
She must've been thrown off
in that moment.

360
00:15:33,360 --> 00:15:34,490
- Right. - In that case,

361
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:35,820
of course Hu picked up on it.

362
00:15:35,840 --> 00:15:36,420
Exactly.

363
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:40,490
Cong.

364
00:15:40,960 --> 00:15:42,220
Listen, you didn't just bust

365
00:15:42,440 --> 00:15:44,820
a drug smuggler today.

366
00:15:44,870 --> 00:15:46,220
You also saved the confidence

367
00:15:46,240 --> 00:15:48,770
of a top-notch drug sniffer dog.

368
00:15:49,320 --> 00:15:50,460
I just wrapped the case.

369
00:15:50,480 --> 00:15:51,610
How'd you already know?

370
00:15:51,750 --> 00:15:53,610
My wife told me, obviously.

371
00:15:53,630 --> 00:15:55,650
Look at you, busting suspects and…

372
00:15:55,670 --> 00:15:56,530
Mr. Shen!

373
00:15:56,630 --> 00:15:57,580
Where is everyone?

374
00:16:07,440 --> 00:16:08,850
I was just at the door

375
00:16:09,390 --> 00:16:11,940
and could already hear you
running your mouth.

376
00:16:16,270 --> 00:16:17,060
I'll keep it brief.

377
00:16:17,270 --> 00:16:18,100
After

378
00:16:18,240 --> 00:16:20,130
we tore the carpet apart,

379
00:16:20,150 --> 00:16:20,890
we found

380
00:16:21,600 --> 00:16:23,530
3,492 grams

381
00:16:24,080 --> 00:16:25,060
of heroin.

382
00:16:26,510 --> 00:16:27,530
This is

383
00:16:27,960 --> 00:16:30,130
the largest single drug smuggling case

384
00:16:30,670 --> 00:16:31,890
Binhai Passenger Inspection

385
00:16:31,910 --> 00:16:33,530
has handled this year.

386
00:16:34,150 --> 00:16:35,130
Section I just…

387
00:16:37,480 --> 00:16:38,300
made a major bust.

388
00:16:43,360 --> 00:16:44,010
Good job.

389
00:16:44,600 --> 00:16:45,460
But it's also a wake-up call.

390
00:16:45,480 --> 00:16:46,060
Cong,

391
00:16:46,360 --> 00:16:48,530
I need you to

392
00:16:48,550 --> 00:16:49,890
put together a full report ASAP,

393
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:53,010
covering the full process
and your reasoning.

394
00:16:53,360 --> 00:16:55,610
We'll report it to the GACC right away

395
00:16:55,840 --> 00:16:58,130
and alert all other ports

396
00:16:58,550 --> 00:17:01,300
to watch for this
new concealment method.

397
00:17:01,320 --> 00:17:01,730
Yes, sir.

398
00:17:10,480 --> 00:17:14,160
[Customs Dormitory]

399
00:17:25,480 --> 00:17:25,740
[Customs officers intercepted a man
at Haparanda Station in February,]

400
00:17:25,740 --> 00:17:26,000
[who had traveled from Örebro.]

401
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:26,300
[Two kilograms of amphetamine
were found in his backpack,]

402
00:17:26,300 --> 00:17:26,660
[which led to the uncovering of
a criminal network in northern Sweden.]

403
00:17:26,660 --> 00:17:27,160
[Five individuals were charged.]

404
00:17:36,200 --> 00:17:37,060
[Nov. 15, 2023: French Customs seized
over one ton of cocaine concealed.]

405
00:17:37,060 --> 00:17:38,000
[Nov. 20, 2023: French Customs
seized 20,000 ancient artifacts.]

406
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:38,360
[International News Roundup]

407
00:17:38,360 --> 00:17:38,900
[Nov. 8, 2023: FCS of Russia
seized 225 kg of smuggled gold.]

408
00:17:38,900 --> 00:17:39,760
[Nov. 10, 2023: Russian Customs
intercepted smuggled alcohol.]

409
00:18:12,030 --> 00:18:13,490
The coffee is on another level.

410
00:18:13,720 --> 00:18:14,700
Obviously.

411
00:18:15,030 --> 00:18:16,570
Li brought it back herself.

412
00:18:17,200 --> 00:18:17,980
It's called...

413
00:18:19,110 --> 00:18:20,490
Whatever, it's just really good coffee.

414
00:18:23,200 --> 00:18:23,700
Li,

415
00:18:24,480 --> 00:18:25,770
you've spoiled my taste.

416
00:18:25,790 --> 00:18:27,380
I can't afford to keep this up.

417
00:18:27,400 --> 00:18:29,140
Then don't drink coffee.

418
00:18:29,310 --> 00:18:30,730
Go for tap water.

419
00:18:33,160 --> 00:18:34,460
Stop whining about money.

420
00:18:35,030 --> 00:18:35,810
Go on.

421
00:18:36,400 --> 00:18:37,050
Li.

422
00:18:37,790 --> 00:18:39,620
Christmas and New Year are coming up.

423
00:18:39,720 --> 00:18:41,810
Best time to move the product.

424
00:18:42,070 --> 00:18:43,050
Are we really sitting this out?

425
00:18:43,440 --> 00:18:45,810
I talked it over with Mr. E.

426
00:18:46,240 --> 00:18:48,180
He said we stay off the airport route

427
00:18:48,200 --> 00:18:49,460
until the doll situation

428
00:18:49,750 --> 00:18:51,250
is cleared up.

429
00:18:51,590 --> 00:18:52,380
But I think

430
00:18:52,400 --> 00:18:53,620
we should keep things moving.

431
00:18:53,830 --> 00:18:54,420
True.

432
00:18:54,440 --> 00:18:55,900
We can't have everyone broke
over the holidays.

433
00:18:56,350 --> 00:18:57,140
Understood.

434
00:18:58,030 --> 00:19:00,380
Keep your people overseas

435
00:19:00,400 --> 00:19:01,530
tight and ready.

436
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:03,330
Ready to move at any time.

437
00:19:03,920 --> 00:19:04,620
Li,

438
00:19:04,880 --> 00:19:06,460
I've got that covered.

439
00:19:06,590 --> 00:19:08,290
It's just the funds…

440
00:19:08,400 --> 00:19:09,620
So you need money, huh?

441
00:19:10,590 --> 00:19:12,250
Fine, I'll transfer it tomorrow.

442
00:19:13,270 --> 00:19:14,620
Cool. Thanks.

443
00:19:15,590 --> 00:19:16,530
I'll get back to it.

444
00:19:17,750 --> 00:19:18,660
See ya.

445
00:19:18,960 --> 00:19:19,620
Xiao Dabao.

446
00:19:25,550 --> 00:19:26,730
Bye, Hua.

447
00:19:30,750 --> 00:19:30,940
I...

448
00:19:30,960 --> 00:19:31,220
You...

449
00:19:32,440 --> 00:19:34,860
Stop staring. Quit messing with him.

450
00:19:35,350 --> 00:19:37,570
At least we should look like a team.

451
00:19:37,920 --> 00:19:38,900
I get it.

452
00:19:39,510 --> 00:19:40,250
But Li,

453
00:19:40,270 --> 00:19:41,620
you don't have to be so nice to him.

454
00:19:41,790 --> 00:19:43,490
He's always coming up
with new ways to ask for money.

455
00:19:43,790 --> 00:19:45,050
And every time he says 'Xiao Dabao',

456
00:19:45,070 --> 00:19:45,980
it sounds like 'baby'!

457
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:47,290
He's the baby!

458
00:19:47,480 --> 00:19:48,330
Enough.

459
00:19:48,550 --> 00:19:49,620
If I don't use him,

460
00:19:49,720 --> 00:19:50,770
are you gonna deal with

461
00:19:50,790 --> 00:19:52,140
all those foreigners yourself?

462
00:19:52,590 --> 00:19:53,250
I'm being nice

463
00:19:53,270 --> 00:19:56,010
because a good tool
makes the job easier.

464
00:19:58,590 --> 00:19:59,140
Li,

465
00:19:59,720 --> 00:20:00,860
everything I know

466
00:20:00,920 --> 00:20:02,380
wouldn't fill half your coffee cup.

467
00:20:02,680 --> 00:20:03,810
Can you just say it straight?

468
00:20:04,480 --> 00:20:05,860
What I mean is,

469
00:20:06,270 --> 00:20:07,570
we're the family.

470
00:20:07,790 --> 00:20:09,810
He's just a tool we use to make money.

471
00:20:10,310 --> 00:20:11,980
Ken's sharp.

472
00:20:12,030 --> 00:20:13,250
Let him be the one out front.

473
00:20:13,480 --> 00:20:14,490
You just sit back

474
00:20:14,510 --> 00:20:16,010
and enjoy life. Isn't that perfect?

475
00:20:17,960 --> 00:20:19,700
Well, if you put it that way,

476
00:20:21,680 --> 00:20:23,250
I feel a lot better.

477
00:20:26,270 --> 00:20:27,140
Hold on, Li.

478
00:20:28,550 --> 00:20:29,860
I just remembered,

479
00:20:30,520 --> 00:20:31,980
three years ago,
Group E started falling apart

480
00:20:32,040 --> 00:20:33,620
because of those dolls.

481
00:20:34,030 --> 00:20:35,700
And now they're showing up again.

482
00:20:36,110 --> 00:20:37,250
Think they're coming after us?

483
00:20:37,510 --> 00:20:38,860
I don't care where they came from.

484
00:20:38,920 --> 00:20:40,490
I'm not repeating Sa Ziyi's mistake.

485
00:20:40,510 --> 00:20:41,700
Of course not.

486
00:20:42,510 --> 00:20:45,180
But Mr. E…

487
00:20:45,830 --> 00:20:46,900
He's looking into it, too.

488
00:20:47,110 --> 00:20:48,810
I think he wants to know

489
00:20:48,830 --> 00:20:50,420
where those dolls
came from even more than I do.

490
00:20:50,550 --> 00:20:51,330
Why's that?

491
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:52,730
Hard to say.

492
00:20:52,830 --> 00:20:53,250
I just have a feeling

493
00:20:53,270 --> 00:20:56,660
these aren't quite like
the ones from three years ago.

494
00:21:01,720 --> 00:21:02,460
Guo Cong.

495
00:21:03,110 --> 00:21:03,900
Shen Taotao.

496
00:21:07,440 --> 00:21:08,140
Need something?

497
00:21:08,680 --> 00:21:10,490
Can't I just drop by and say hi?

498
00:21:12,720 --> 00:21:13,770
So what is it?

499
00:21:14,680 --> 00:21:15,660
Well,

500
00:21:15,720 --> 00:21:17,860
something's wrong with my car.

501
00:21:18,040 --> 00:21:20,460
The rear tire pressure warning
keeps popping up.

502
00:21:20,960 --> 00:21:22,530
I don't feel safe driving it.

503
00:21:22,920 --> 00:21:24,140
Can I

504
00:21:24,270 --> 00:21:25,290
catch a ride with you?

505
00:21:27,510 --> 00:21:28,940
Where'd you park?

506
00:21:30,790 --> 00:21:31,810
Over there,

507
00:21:31,830 --> 00:21:33,250
in the airline staff lot.

508
00:21:33,550 --> 00:21:34,180
Let's go take a look?

509
00:21:38,310 --> 00:21:39,530
Hey, Tao, Mr. Guo.

510
00:21:39,550 --> 00:21:40,460
You two still here?

511
00:21:40,510 --> 00:21:41,010
I'm heading out.

512
00:21:41,030 --> 00:21:42,010
Bye.

513
00:21:45,280 --> 00:21:46,010
Nice car.

514
00:21:46,270 --> 00:21:47,620
Nobody bought it for me.

515
00:21:47,680 --> 00:21:49,010
I financed it myself.

516
00:22:00,720 --> 00:22:01,220
Keys.

517
00:22:10,110 --> 00:22:11,860
See? Something's off.

518
00:22:13,270 --> 00:22:14,010
Let me check the tire.

519
00:22:17,480 --> 00:22:17,980
Whoa.

520
00:22:24,440 --> 00:22:25,570
Looks fine to me.

521
00:22:26,350 --> 00:22:28,420
I still don't think
I should drive today.

522
00:22:28,760 --> 00:22:30,010
Can I catch a ride with you?

523
00:22:31,680 --> 00:22:32,810
I'm thinking

524
00:22:32,830 --> 00:22:35,290
it might be
a dashboard calibration issue.

525
00:22:35,520 --> 00:22:37,180
Why don't you take it to the dealership

526
00:22:37,440 --> 00:22:38,490
and have the pros check it out?

527
00:22:38,720 --> 00:22:39,900
I'm not driving it.

528
00:22:39,960 --> 00:22:42,220
Tire issues are no joke.

529
00:22:44,920 --> 00:22:46,570
Someone in our department

530
00:22:46,800 --> 00:22:48,010
is great with cars.

531
00:22:48,160 --> 00:22:49,140
I'll call him over.

532
00:22:49,270 --> 00:22:50,460
That's really not necessary.

533
00:22:50,520 --> 00:22:51,530
I'll just have someone

534
00:22:51,600 --> 00:22:52,660
from the dealership swing by.

535
00:22:52,750 --> 00:22:54,010
No, let him check it out.

536
00:22:54,160 --> 00:22:55,010
If he can fix it,

537
00:22:55,080 --> 00:22:55,980
that'll save you the trouble.

538
00:22:56,160 --> 00:22:57,180
It's really fine.

539
00:22:57,760 --> 00:22:59,250
Just give me a ride into town.

540
00:22:59,720 --> 00:23:00,460
No, no.

541
00:23:00,520 --> 00:23:01,530
This is serious.

542
00:23:01,640 --> 00:23:02,730
Safety comes first.

543
00:23:04,120 --> 00:23:05,050
So,

544
00:23:05,280 --> 00:23:06,900
you're actually worried about me.

545
00:23:07,720 --> 00:23:09,810
Nobody should get hurt, right?

546
00:23:10,320 --> 00:23:11,620
Done, told him.

547
00:23:11,720 --> 00:23:12,620
He's on his way.

548
00:23:12,680 --> 00:23:13,290
Just hang tight.

549
00:23:13,310 --> 00:23:13,980
I'm leaving.

550
00:23:14,200 --> 00:23:15,330
You're leaving?

551
00:23:15,400 --> 00:23:16,460
Come on, stay with me.

552
00:23:16,520 --> 00:23:18,010
He's coming from the terminal.

553
00:23:18,080 --> 00:23:19,090
Two minutes.

554
00:23:19,160 --> 00:23:20,010
Just stay, okay?

555
00:23:20,080 --> 00:23:22,010
You can't even wait two minutes with me?

556
00:23:22,080 --> 00:23:22,860
I'm busy.

557
00:23:22,880 --> 00:23:23,530
Bye.

558
00:23:29,270 --> 00:23:30,250
Still not here?

559
00:23:30,790 --> 00:23:32,180
Hang on. I'll call him.

560
00:23:32,510 --> 00:23:33,090
Bye.

561
00:23:39,790 --> 00:23:40,980
Bowen, any update?

562
00:23:41,070 --> 00:23:41,730
Did you figure it out?

563
00:23:41,960 --> 00:23:42,770
What's wrong with her car?

564
00:23:43,310 --> 00:23:43,810
Mr. Guo,

565
00:23:45,520 --> 00:23:47,220
I was just about to call you.
I'm at 068.

566
00:23:47,550 --> 00:23:49,180
I don't see Shen Taotao anywhere.

567
00:23:49,550 --> 00:23:51,180
I've looped the lot a few times already.

568
00:24:05,240 --> 00:24:05,900
Xiaoyan,

569
00:24:05,960 --> 00:24:06,570
Mentor.

570
00:24:06,590 --> 00:24:07,330
You know what time it is?

571
00:24:07,720 --> 00:24:08,490
Coming.

572
00:24:08,510 --> 00:24:09,620
Get changed, quick.

573
00:24:09,680 --> 00:24:10,290
Got it!

574
00:24:17,030 --> 00:24:17,620
Yu,

575
00:24:17,750 --> 00:24:18,730
did you hear?

